        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Tomato Egg</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 large eggs</li>
            <li>2 medium tomatoes, chopped</li>
            <li>1 onion, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ginger, grated</li>
            <li>1 green chili, chopped (optional)</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground coriander</li>
            <li>Salt, to taste</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat. Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.</li>
            <li>Add sliced onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.</li>
            <li>Stir in minced garlic, grated ginger, and chopped green chili. Sauté for 1-2 minutes until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Add chopped tomatoes to the pan. Cook until the tomatoes are soft and the oil starts to separate.</li>
            <li>Season with turmeric powder, red chili powder, ground coriander, and salt. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Make wells in the tomato mixture and crack the eggs into the wells. Cook until the egg whites are set but the yolks are still runny (or to your desired doneness).</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve the Tomato Egg hot with rice or bread.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Tomato Egg dish!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

